- Tapas have evolved from their original form and are now served in larger portions.
- The tradition of serving tapas has changed to accommodate modern dining preferences for more substantial meals.
- Restaurants may offer tapas as a main course option, increasing portion sizes to satisfy customers.
- The concept of tapas has been adapted in different regions to include larger servings.
- Tapas are sometimes combined to create a full meal experience, making them more filling.
- The popularity of tapas has led to variations that include more generous servings.